---
description: Database and financial integrity requirements
globs: ["**/*.sql", "supabase/**", "services/**", "packages/domain/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

- PostgreSQL 16+.
- Use UUID internal identifiers and numeric monetary columns; never floating-point money.
- Derive organization and clinic from authenticated server context.
- Posted clinical and financial records are reversed, voided or superseded, not hard-deleted.
- Use explicit transactions, row locks, idempotency and immutable audit.
- Preserve separate facts for bills, collections, allocations, advances, exposure, refunds and reversals.
- Do not implement uncertain financial behavior without a decision record.
